{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "stage4b-demo-collection",
    "name": "Stage4B-Demo",
    "description": "HNG14 Stage 4B – Insighta Labs+ backend demo collection.\n\nCovers:\n- Auth (admin + analyst tokens via shortcut routes)\n- API version and auth guards\n- Profile list / search / export\n- Cache / performance demo\n- CSV import (valid, mixed, duplicate, analyst 403)\n- Cache invalidation demo\n- Create / delete (admin-only)\n\nBefore running:\n1. Import Stage4B-Local environment\n2. Start the server: npm start (port 3000)\n3. Run folder A – Setup/Auth first\n\nAll tokens expire in 180 s. Re-run folder A if you get 401.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "A – Setup / Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "0 – Verify server connection (GET /)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// RUNS FIRST. If this fails, Postman is not reaching the server.",
                  "// Check: (1) server is running  npm start, (2) Stage4B-Local environment is",
                  "// selected in Postman (top-right dropdown), (3) baseUrl = http://localhost:3000",
                  "const baseUrl = pm.environment.get('baseUrl');",
                  "console.log('baseUrl is:', baseUrl);",
                  "pm.test('baseUrl is set (not blank)', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(baseUrl).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('API is reachable', () => pm.expect(body.status).to.eql('success'));",
                  "if (pm.response.code !== 200) {",
                  "  console.error('SERVER NOT REACHABLE. All subsequent tests will fail.');",
                  "  console.error('Make sure: (1) npm start is running, (2) Stage4B-Local env is selected.');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": [""]
            },
            "description": "RUN THIS FIRST. Checks that the server is reachable and the Stage4B-Local environment is selected.\n\nIf this fails:\n1. Start the server: npm start (from the repo root)\n2. In Postman, click the environment dropdown (top-right) and select 'Stage4B-Local'\n3. If the environment is not listed, import postman/Stage4B-Local.postman_environment.json"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Admin login (GET shortcut)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "// Accept multiple token shapes",
                  "const token = body.access_token || body.accessToken || body.token",
                  "  || (body.data && (body.data.access_token || body.data.accessToken || body.data.token));",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('access_token present', () => pm.expect(token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
                  "pm.test('role is admin', () => {",
                  "  const role = body.role || body.user_role || body.userRole || (body.user && body.user.role);",
                  "  pm.expect(role).to.eql('admin');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.environment.set('adminAccessToken', token);",
                  "pm.environment.set('accessToken', token);",
                  "console.log('Admin token saved, first 40:', token.substring(0,40));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/admin",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "admin"]
            },
            "description": "Uses the /auth/admin shortcut route to get an admin JWT. Saves as adminAccessToken and accessToken."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Analyst login (GET shortcut)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "const token = body.access_token || body.accessToken || body.token",
                  "  || (body.data && (body.data.access_token || body.data.accessToken || body.data.token));",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('access_token present', () => pm.expect(token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
                  "pm.test('role is analyst', () => {",
                  "  const role = body.role || body.user_role || body.userRole || (body.user && body.user.role);",
                  "  pm.expect(role).to.eql('analyst');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.environment.set('analystAccessToken', token);",
                  "console.log('Analyst token saved, first 40:', token.substring(0,40));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/analyst",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "analyst"]
            },
            "description": "Uses /auth/analyst shortcut to get an analyst JWT. Saves as analystAccessToken."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Admin login via POST test-login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "const token = body.access_token || body.accessToken || body.token",
                  "  || (body.data && (body.data.access_token || body.data.accessToken || body.data.token));",
                  "pm.test('token returned', () => pm.expect(token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
                  "// Optionally override adminAccessToken with this token",
                  "// pm.environment.set('adminAccessToken', token);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\"role\": \"admin\", \"username\": \"test_admin\"}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/test-login",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "test-login"]
            },
            "description": "Alternative POST route for graders that test POST-based auth. Requires the server at {{baseUrl}} to be reachable and the Stage4B-Local environment to be selected.\n\nIf this returns 'Profile not found': the environment is not selected or baseUrl is wrong. Run request '0 – Verify server connection' first."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
